```

## Screen Dimensions Hook

```tsx
import { useWindowDimensions } from "react-native";

export function useResponsive() {
  const { width, height } = useWindowDimensions();
  return {
    isPhone: width < 768,
    isTablet: width >= 768 && width < 1024,
    isLandscape: width > height,
    width,
    height,
  };
}
```

## Conventions

- Type navigation and route with project `ParamList`
- `useFocusEffect` with `useCallback` to avoid re-renders
- AsyncStorage: always handle `null` and serialize with JSON
- Screen hooks: one hook per screen to encapsulate navigation + data
- Return named object (never array/tuple) for clarity
